Louis REINACH, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 7016. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 8, 1934. Rene A. Viosca, U. S. Atty., and William H. Norman, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of New Orleans, La.

Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and WALKER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This is an appeal from a judgment of conviction for violations of the National Prohibition Aet (27 USCA). Upon the authority of United States v. Chamber, 54 S. Ct. 434, 78 L. Ed. —, opinion filed February 5,1934, the judgment is reversed and annulled.
